Rebuild the entire index by re-scanning all log files.

This is useful when:
  - You suspect the index is corrupted
  - Provider log formats have changed
  - You want to force re-processing of all sessions

Warning: This clears all existing index data.

Usage: agtrace index rebuild [OPTIONS]

Options:
      --provider <PROVIDER>
          Filter by provider
          
          [default: all]
          [possible values: claude_code, codex, gemini, all]

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

Output Options:
      --quiet
          Minimal output (IDs only, for scripting)

      --compact
          Compact output (one line per item)

      --verbose
          Verbose output (all metadata)

Global Options:
      --data-dir <DATA_DIR>
          Directory for agtrace database and configuration (defaults to system data directory, or AGTRACE_PATH env var)

      --format <FORMAT>
          Output format for command results
          
          [default: plain]
          [possible values: plain, json]

      --log-level <LOG_LEVEL>
          Logging verbosity level
          
          [default: info]
          [possible values: error, warn, info, debug, trace]

      --project-root <PROJECT_ROOT>
          Override project root directory (defaults to current directory)

      --all-projects
          Operate on all indexed projects instead of current project only
